flowRoot.flowPara: With stimulus-reaction-habits, for example if you get always a reward (m8, see also card b1, b2, b3, t1...) and after 1000 repetitions you will get punishment instead of a reward (m7) things like this could happen. But the problem is if one has something like a spinal cord implant, then the whole reward /punishment thing becomes obsolete. So in both cases Windows / Computers can produce people that run amok. But with spinal-cord remote controlled he would not be the real murderer, and you can not blame only him, because the person that remote controlled him would just kill with the next "BOT". Try to find bot, the BOT and the person that tries to make the "BOT" run amok. https://marclandolt.ch/ml_buzzernet/2016/04/25/vorstufe-zu-breivik/
